                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.30/181: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-04T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 4, 1942—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>413. Your 967, July 3, 6 p.m. It is true that our 411, July 3, 1 a.m. was sent
                    before receiving your 962 of July 2, 7 p.m.</p>
                <p>Department’s 411 of July 3, 1 a.m. transmits the President’s proposal as he
                    wishes it to be laid before the French Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
